Rating: 4
After I made this for us for dinner tonight, and we had enough left-over for at least one more night, my fiance said the only suggestion he had to improve this stew was that I should double this recipe next time so we have more leftovers! So it gets 4 forks from me! I basically followed the recipe but took the suggestions of the many other reviewers who suggested a bit less liquid (I used 6 cups total - 1 c of that was stout beer). I also threw everything in the crock pot (first I browned the meat and put it in the crock pot with the liquids, then I browned the vegetables in the same dutch oven I used to brown the meat, and added those to the meat in the crock pot), and cooked it for several hours. After about 4 hours in the crock pot (2 hrs on high, 2 hrs on low), the stew was very thick the way we like it, and the meat was fall apart tender. This was good and simple (not bland) and we thought it was delicious with some french bread. This is our favorite beef stew recipe now :)

Rating: 3
This is a great base, but is much improved by a few modifications, as suggested by other reviewers. I sprinkle a couple generous tablespoons of flour over the beef towards the end of the browning process, then deglaze the pot with a good splash of red wine and reduce the liquid to 5 cups, while replacing 2 of the cups of stock with a can of Guinness or other stout. I also add a few handfuls of frozen baby peas at the end. Great, warming meal for a cold winter's night!

