I gave it 3 forks since I took a lot of suggestions below and changed the recipe too much to rate it as is. I doubled the beef (for the kids who eat the beef but won't touch the vegetables), used about 2lbs potatoes instead of 3 and left out the parsley. I completely agree with everyone that there is far too much liquid as written. I used 4 cups of beef stock and 1 cup of red wine and there was still plenty of sauce to dip bread in. I also rolled the beef in a combination of flour, pepper, and an irish garden herb mix (a combination of thyme, rosemary, basil and chives) and browned the meat before adding the other ingredients (except vegetables). Then I baked at 275 for 1 1/2 hours before adding the vegetables and baking for another hour. I didn't bother to saute the vegetables before adding to the stew.

