Like many others, I made some changes... I upped the quantity of everything for more stew, but I also: tossed the beef in flour with thyme and oregano before browning (in extra virgin olive oil, for a little more character and richness) Upped the worcestershire content to 3+ TBSP and made the sugar brown Added some other herbs to the stock, notably basil and oregano. Added almost 2 cups of a good cabernet sauvignon, and used it to deglaze the pot after browning the beef. Increased the vegetables, made the potatoes red, added celery and thick-sliced button mushrooms. I also think that next time I will ROAST the vegetables rather than sauté to increase the earthy, rich flavor even more. Maybe with some rosemary. With the increased amount of vegetables, I increased the amount of butter to 4 TBSP. This was a delicious stew, and I plan to keep the modified recipe around for a long time.

