Rating: 3
The suggestions in the reviews of this recipe have really perfected it. The first time I made it, I followed the recipe as is, except substituting a Guinness for some of the stock. It was fine. The second time, I made the following changes: (1) doubled the amount of meat and tomato paste; (2) reduced the amount of thyme; (3) reduced the potatoes to 2 lbs; (4) reduced the stock to 4 cups and added a Guinness; (5) added 1/2 cup celery; (6) dredged the meat in flour before frying; (7) prepared the stew in the morning and reheated in the evening. The new version was delicious, a major improvement. A great winter meal for everyone, especially the meat-and-potatoes crowd; very satisfying. (PS I definitely recommend saute-ing the vegetables, even though it's extra work; it really livens up the flavor and makes it more complex.)

