This is so simple, it's hard ro figure out why it tastes so good, but it does. If your meat isn't browning, you're probably putting too many pieces in the pot. If they touch each other, they stew, not brown. Use tongs and do a few pieces at a time, removing them as they brown. I couldn't get the veggies to brown, though. Pan too crowded maybe? Stew was still good, though.

