Rating: 4
Here is the problem people are having: You are not cooking this long enough! Cook it 40 minutes to an hour more than what the recipe calls for and it will thicken on its own, no thickening agent necessary. The starch in the potatoes will thicken the stew, just be patient. It will also be thicker and tastier if you make it a day ahead of time. I made the recipe as is, with the exception of dredging the beef in flour before browning and doubling the beef amount, and it was wonderful. Next time I will cut the potatoes larger (they disintergrate a bit from cooking so long)and add turnips or parsnips for variety.

