Rating: 3
Just like my grandmother used to make. I don't understand why some folks need to flour the beef. If you simply remove all the moisture from the beef first (pat dry with paper towels) it will brown just fine. The sauce should thicken on its own from two things: 1) from being reduced and 2) from the starch in the potatoes...if that doesn't happen, you probably haven't cooked the stew with the potatoes long enough.

