I altered the recipe slightly based on previous reviews and it came out great, my family LOVED it! I too dredged the meat in seasoned flour first. I added some red wine, used a little over 2 lbs. of meat, about 1 cup of potatoes and more carrots, no parsley (didn't have any.) The only thing is, it seemed kind of salty, maybe from the Worcestershire Sauce? I used beef "Better than Bouillon" for the beef stock. The gravy came out nice and thick, I didn't even have to worry about thickening it, and simmered it for a total of about 3 hours, meat came out nice and tender. Didn't even have to skim the fat, I had used very lean meat from the butcher. Real keeper, will make this again!

