Rating: 4
A great, hearty stew with my modifications: I use two pounds of beef (it's beef stew, after all!), using sirloin tips to improve the quality. I *definitely* add a good dose of red wine to brighten it up (about 1/3 a bottle). I leave the peels on the potatoes and carrots to make it heartier and tastier. I usually just sautee a couple of vine-ripened tomatoes instead of the paste, and because I like it thick, I add only about 2/3 to 3/4 of the stock called for. I also add some sliced shitake mushrooms for the last fifteen to twenty minutes. Also, you must must must let this baby simmer for a good two and a half to three hours -- it's amazing what a long stew will do for the taste. This is a often-requested meal that lasts for days.

Rating: 2
Very 'blah', even though I used homemade stock and added lots of salt and pepper. Defintely reduce oil to 1 T for browning. Ratio of potatoes to beef is very high. Need to add more spices if you like stew with any taste. I added flour to get a better consistency (2 T dissolved in stew stock)

