Chicago - the ingredient you can't put your finger on is a nice little slug of red wine ! Transforms any beef stew. I also put in the juice of one orange & a few shakes of Tabasco sauce, fresh parsley sprigs & much less liquid. Cooking a stew in the oven at a low heat (325) also makes for a better dish IMO. My recipe is from Arabella Boxer's winter cookery book & is the best beef stew I've ever made or tasted.

